
Jeppe Olsen is professor of chemistry at Aarhus University 
(Denmark). He received his Ph.D in Chemistry from University of Aarhus 
and was postdoc at Texas A & M University  with Danny L. Yeager and 
at University of Utah with Jack Simons. From 1986 to 1998 he was employed 
at Lund University and returned to Aarhus University in 1998.
His main research interests
are the development of ab initio methods for the study of molecular
structure and properties, including high accuracy methods for small 
molecules, methods for large molecules, and relativistic contributions.
He is an author of the Dalton, Dirac, MOLCAS and LUCIA programs.
